# Example environment variables (top-level files: .env*).
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in real values. Real `.env` / `.env.local`
# files are GIT-IGNORED — only this `.env.example` is committed, so teammates know
# which variables exist without leaking secrets.
#
# Variables prefixed with NEXT_PUBLIC_ are exposed to the browser.
# Everything else is server-only.

NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_NAME="Next.js Structure Lab"
EXAMPLE_SERVER_SECRET="replace-me-in-.env.local"
